HEADWORD: Tetrahexahedron
<hw>Tet`ra*hex`a*he"dron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tetra-</ets> + <ets>hexahedron</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A solid in the isometric system, bounded
by twenty-four equal triangular faces, four corresponding to each face
of the cube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>tetrahydrocannabinol</ent>⟦br⟧
